  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SUPPORTING MEASURES TO MONITOR AND EFFECTINVELY PREVENT HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN RWANDAN PRISONS AND DETENTION CENTRES</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to tackle human rights abuses that go on in Rwandan prisons and detention centres. The project will train 15 prison personnel (including 10 prison officers and 5 prison workers from the Rwanda Correctional Services), the project will also train 30 volunteers who will educate, monitor and report on human rights abuses. Training will focus on human rights and prevention of human rights abuses in prisons and detention facilities. The project will contribute to strengthening of the rule of law, respectful of human rights and fundamental freedoms, the values and principles of democratic in Rwanda through the promotion of the rights of prisoners and improving prisoners conditions as it provided by national and international legal instruments.</narrative>
  </description>
